cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "gale-shapley-algorithm: A Python implementation of the Gale-Shapley algorithm"
authors:
  - family-names: Dokumaci
    given-names: Oral Ersoy
    email: oral.ersoy.dokumaci@gmail.com
    orcid: null
type: software
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/oedokumaci/gale-shapley-algorithm"
url: "https://oedokumaci.github.io/gale-shapley-algorithm"
abstract: >
  A Python implementation of the Gale-Shapley (Deferred Acceptance) algorithm for
  the stable marriage problem. Provides both a symbolic Algorithm/Proposer/Responder
  API and, via the optional numeric extra, a numpy-backed subpackage with fast GS,
  vectorized stability checks, and stable-matching lattice enumeration.
keywords:
  - gale-shapley
  - deferred-acceptance
  - stable-matching
  - matching-theory
  - two-sided-matching
version: 1.6.0
date-released: "2026-04-17"
